Master Answer:
Seek medical care from a health care provider or local health unit right away. The health unit finder is here. Speak with a nurse anytime by calling HealthlinkBC at 8-1-1. A health care provider will assess the animal's behavior, your immunization history and wound before making recommendations around tetanus or rabies vaccines/immunoglobulin.
